%N A382562 Decimal expansion of Sum_{p prime} 1/(p^2*(p + 1)).
%C A382562 The constant c in the formula Sum_{a,b <= x} omega(f(a,b)) = c * x^2 + O(x*log(x)^4), where omega = A001221, and f(a, b) = gcd(ab, a + b)/gcd(a, b) (Tóth, 2026, p. 4, Corollary 4). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 24 2026
%H A382562 László Tóth, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.20057">On the asymptotic density of the ordered pairs (a,b) of positive integers such that gcd(a*b,a+b) = gcd(a,b)</a>, arXiv:2606.20057 [math.NT], 2026. See p. 10 (Proof of Cor. 4).
%H A382562 <a href="/wiki/Index_to_constants#Start_of_section_P">Index to constants which are prime zeta sums</a> {2,0,1}.
%F A382562 Equals A085548 - A179119.
%F A382562 Equals Sum_{k>=3} (-1)^(k+1) * P(k), where P is the prime zeta function. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 01 2025
